Alter the “From” and “Reply-To” fields in email headers to use fake sender addresses (e.g., random email domains or names) instead of the actual source. This tricks spam filters that check sender authenticity.  

2. **Use Proxy Servers or VPNs**  
Route email sending through proxy servers or Virtual Private Networks (VPNs) to hide the original IP address. This makes it harder for email providers to trace the source back to the original sender.  

