6. **Monitor Network Activity:** Regularly check your network activity logs to detect any unusual behavior.

7. **Disable Remote Management:** If possible, disable remote management features in your router settings to prevent unauthorized access.

8. **Use a Firewall:** Enable a firewall on your router to block unauthorized access attempts.

9. **Regularly Update Software:** Keep all software and applications running on your devices up to date to protect against new threats.

10. **Educate Users:** Inform all users about the importance of securing their Wi-Fi networks and the risks associated with weak passwords and unsecured networks.

